Q5/- What is the Difference between the sleep and join method .

ANs:-
-----

Sleep:-
-------

-- if two or more thread are working on same object and we want some delay in the some thread then 
   we can use Thread.sleep which results to delay in thread to execute by some given time.
   
Join:-
------
-- if two or more thread are working on same object and we want to completely execute first thread followed by 
   second thread then we can use Thread.join which results second threaad execting start after first thread completed.
       